article.headline: UTEP 94, Rutgers 68
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Omar Thomas scored 18 points to lead Texas-El Paso to a 94-68 victory over Rutgers in the championship game of the Sierra Providence SunClassic tournament Sunday night. Thomas, who was named the tournament's MVP, shot 8-of-12 from the field and pulled down nine rebounds. He was one of six UTEP players in double figures. The Miners (9-1) jumped out to a 16-0 lead and were never threatened. UTEP held Rutgers, which missed its first 11 shots, scoreless for the first 7:18. The Miners extended their lead to 36-6 on a John Tofi layup with 6:06 left in the first half en route to a commanding 48-13 halftime lead. Roy Smallwood scored 15 points for UTEP (9-1) and had 10 rebounds. Fili Rivera had 14 points and eight assists. Jason Williams and Chris Craig each had 11 points apiece and Tofi added 10. Rutgers (7-2) was led by Herve Lamizana, who scored 17 points but was just 4-of-14 from the floor. Ricky Shields scored 12 points and Calvin Wooten added 11. UTEP's defense forced Rutgers into 22 turnovers.
